      <p class="roast-notes">The bean is roasted less, so it keeps more natural flavours. More acidity, less bitterness. This is why light-roasted Araku tastes fruity — the roaster lets the bean speak for itself.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:6px;margin-bottom:12px;">
        <span class="rtag">Fruit</span><span class="rtag">Floral</span><span class="rtag">Bright</span><span class="rtag">Tea-like</span>
