    <p><strong>Common myth: Dark roast = more caffeine.</strong> Actually the opposite is true. Caffeine is partially destroyed by heat. Light roast has slightly more caffeine. But the taste difference is far more dramatic than the caffeine difference — choose by taste, not caffeine level.</p>
