  <div class="brew-grid">
    <div class="brew-card">
      <div class="brew-header">
        <div class="brew-name">🪣 South Indian Filter</div>
        <span class="brew-difficulty">Easy</span>
      </div>
      <div class="brew-stats">
        <div class="brew-stat"><strong>₹200–600</strong>Device Cost</div>
        <div class="brew-stat"><strong>15–20 min</strong>Brew Time</div>
      </div>
      <p class="brew-text">A two-chamber metal device. Hot water passes through ground coffee slowly to create a thick, concentrated decoction. Mixed with hot milk and sugar. India's oldest and most beloved method.</p>
      <div class="brew-perfect">✓ Perfect for: Thick, strong, milky coffee at home</div>
    </div>

    <div class="brew-card">
      <div class="brew-header">
        <div class="brew-name">🫖 French Press</div>
        <span class="brew-difficulty">Easy</span>
      </div>
      <div class="brew-stats">
        <div class="brew-stat"><strong>₹800–2,500</strong>Device Cost</div>
        <div class="brew-stat"><strong>4 min</strong>Brew Time</div>
      </div>
      <p class="brew-text">Add coarse-ground coffee, pour hot water, wait 4 minutes, press the plunger. No paper filters — oils stay in the cup giving you a thick, full-bodied, rich coffee. Very easy for beginners.</p>
      <div class="brew-perfect">✓ Perfect for: Rich, full-bodied coffee without big investment</div>
    </div>

    <div class="brew-card">
      <div class="brew-header">
        <div class="brew-name">☕ Moka Pot</div>
        <span class="brew-difficulty">Easy</span>
